Sometimes the processor hangs and cause the whole crawling system stop working. I think adding `process_time_limit` to the functions can help us for better debugging.

I add `process_time_limit` to `BaseHandler.process_fields` and use `pyspider.libs.utils.timeout` in `BaseHandler._run_func`.

Then such function can raise an `TimeoutError` when it takes a long time to process.

```
@config(age=10 * 24 * 60 * 60, process_time_limit=3)
    def index_page(self, response):
        time.sleep(2)
        for each in response.doc('a[href^="http"]').items():
            self.crawl(each.attr.href, callback=self.detail_page)
```

This PR is an enhancement which allows for health check of any number of celery queues.
The requirement is that a user specifies a CELERY_QUEUES setting in their settings file, e.g.:

`CELERY_QUEUES = {
    'default': {
        'exchange': 'default',
        'binding_key': 'default',
        'display_name': 'Celery queue 1'
    },
    'queue2': {
        'exchange': 'queue2',
        'routing_key': 'queue2',
        'display_name': 'Celery queue 2'
    }
}`

If display_name is not specified, the displayed name will default to CeleryHealthCheckDefault or CeleryHealthCheckQueue2 (i.e. using the key of the dictionary)

This enables passing one `options` dict to different jsonld functions, for example:

``` python
my_options = {'documentLoader': my_document_loader}
framed = jsonld.frame(doc, frame, options=options)
compacted = jsonld.compact(framed, ctx, options=options)
```

Minimal example of use case that was failing:

``` python
#!/usr/bin/env python

from lib.pyld import jsonld


def my_document_loader(url):
    return jsonld.load_document(url)


doc = {
    'http://schema.org/name': 'Manu Sporny',
    'http://schema.org/url': {'@id': 'http://manu.sporny.org/'},
    'http://schema.org/image':
    {'@id': 'http://manu.sporny.org/images/manu.png'},
}
frame = {
    '@context': 'http://schema.org/',
}
options_orig = {'documentLoader': my_document_loader}
options_new = options_orig.copy()

framed = jsonld.frame(doc, frame, options=options_new)
assert options_orig == options_new
```

